<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Prepare for Herniated Disk Surgery</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="span">A herniated disk occurs</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="2" relname="circumstance">when the cushion between your vertebrae begins to wear down .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="joint">Instead of acting as a cushion ,</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1004" relname="joint">the vertebrae can actually press on nerves ,</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1004" relname="joint">resulting in pain .</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="span">Surgery is necessary for a herniated disk</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="span">if other methods</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="8" relname="purpose">to relieve the back pain do not work .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="span">Preparing for herniated disk surgery is largely a matter</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="10" relname="elaboration">of knowing what to expect .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="sequence">Undergo a physical exam</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1015" relname="span">and complete any tests</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="14" relname="elaboration">deemed necessary by your doctor -- possibly a urine sample and an X-ray .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="span">You &apos;ll also need to supply your medical history .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="16" relname="elaboration">Make sure to note any allergies you have .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="span">Ask your doctor questions</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="joint">you have in regards to your herniated disk surgery</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1020" relname="joint">and fully research the procedure .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1022" relname="span">There are three common types of herniated disc surgery :</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="21" relname="elaboration">laminectomy , corpectomy , and anterior cervical discectomy and fusion .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="sequence">Eat fruits and vegetables ,</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="span">and drink plenty of water in the days and weeks</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="24" relname="elaboration">leading up to your herniated disk surgery .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="span">Adequate hydration will help your body before and after surgery ,</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="26" relname="purpose">so aim for 10 glasses of water per day .</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1012" relname="joint">Take time to rest and relax prior to your herniated disk surgery .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1030" relname="span">Seek help around the house with any chores</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="purpose">so you do n&apos;t re-injure your back prior to surgery .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1012" relname="joint">Stop smoking .</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1012" relname="joint">Smoking can cause surgery complications</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1012" relname="joint">and can lengthen your healing time .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="contrast">Some doctors recommend quitting 6 to 8 weeks prior to surgery ,</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="contrast">while others only insist on no cigarettes for 24 hours prior to surgery .</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1012" relname="joint">Check with your doctor on this issue .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1038" relname="span">Follow the pre-surgery guidelines</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="37" relname="circumstance">as given to you by your doctor .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="preparation">Instructions may include what to eat and drink ,</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1040" relname="joint">as well as whether you &apos;re allowed to take any medications or supplements prior to surgery .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="contrast">Your doctor may require that you only consume clear liquids for several days prior to surgery</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1042" relname="contrast">or may restrict your diet in other ways for 12 to 24 hours prior to surgery .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1040" relname="joint">Plan ahead for an overnight stay at the hospital .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="45" relname="concession">It &apos;s not required in all cases ,</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1045" relname="span">but you make proper arrangements ahead of time just in case .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="span">Plan for your recovery at home</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="span">following your herniated disk surgery .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">You wo n&apos;t be able to drive ,</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="purpose">so find a ride home from the hospital .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1052" relname="span">You may also want someone around</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="50" relname="purpose">to help you at home</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1052" relname="circumstance">as you recover .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1040" relname="joint">Total recovery time should take 6 to 8 weeks .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1055" relname="span">Expect to take time off work</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="54" relname="circumstance">as you recover .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="contrast">The amount of time will depend on how your recovery is progressing .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1058" relname="span">However , you must wait about 6 weeks</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="57" relname="purpose">to do anything other than desk work .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1040" relname="joint">Make contact with a physical therapist</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">and set up appointments for after your surgery</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="60" relname="circumstance">while you are recovering at home .</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1062" relname="joint">Find out how much the procedure will cost</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1062" relname="joint">and what your insurance will cover .</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1062" relname="joint">Make sure you are pre-certified through your insurance carrier before your herniated disk procedure .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1062" relname="joint">You may be able to pay the surgery center over time .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="68" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1066" relname="span">Repairing a herniated disc may require more than one surgery .</segment>
